can any pregnant women relate i am weeks pregnant i feel really guilty about not being able to do as much as i normally do for my other child and husband i feel like they both resent me when i rest or when i ask for help around the house it is really hard for me to ask for help as it is it's not anything in particular that he says but i just get the general impression that my husband is annoyed with me i'm doing the best that i can i feel like they are both just so used to me doing every imaginable thing for them that they're not too happy with me right now i am a perfectionist so i'm not sure if this is just my own guilt because i'm not living up to my own expectations what do you think couple of thoughts your husband might just be tired if your not sleeping well which is common in late pg he may not be sleeping well this is a stressful time for your husband things are going to change a lot point is it may not be about what you are or are not doing with the other child do what you can you don't state the age of your child so some of these ideas might not work but here's some good ways to give that child some extra attention now take a nap together read books watch a movie sit in the shade while s he plays outside do a craft together don't guess about your husband's feelings ask him give yourself a break you need to rest up before the little one arrives you have to have different priorities right now EastEnders Knots Landing Friends The Apprentice 2 Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Crime film Kurt Cobain Theory of conduct Jam (TV series) Summa Theologiae Siesta Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Pitaten English grammar Procrastination Pregnancy Guiding Light Transactional analysis Shaggy dog story About Schmidt Scenes from a Memory Marilyn Monroe Humphrey Bogart Mary I of Scotland Social rule Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Sigmund Freud Sharon Tate David Hume Socrates Anne Boleyn Just Like That The Amber Spyglass Extreme Programming Ty Cobb Scrooge McDuck A Course I